HEADWORD: Riga fir
<hw>Ri"ga fir`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[So called from <ets>Riga</ets>,
a city in Russia.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A species of pine
(<spn>Pinus sylvestris</spn>), and its wood, which affords a valuable
timber; -- called also <altname>Scotch pine</altname>, and <altname>red
deal</altname> <it>or</it> <altname>yellow deal</altname>. It grows in
all parts of Europe, in the Caucasus, and in Siberia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rigarion</ent>⟦br⟧
